/\">7 Best WooCommerce SEO Plugins And Tools to Get More Traffic</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Saud Razzak\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19789:\"<p>Are you looking for the best WooCommerce SEO plugins and tools that could help you to grow your store&#8217;s traffic?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Search is the single largest traffic source for most eCommerce stores. That&#8217;s why you should make sure that your website is properly optimized in all respects so that search engines rank your store in the top results.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this post, we&#8217;ll show you some of the best SEO plugins and tools for WooCommerce that help you drive more organic traffic and sales. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>List of the Top WooCommerce SEO Plugins &amp; Tools</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Here&#8217;re the top <strong>8</strong> WooCommerce SEO plugins and tools that we&#8217;re going to check out so that you can pick the best fit for your store.</p>\n\n\n\n<ol><li><a href=\"#All-in-One-SEO-for-WordPress\">All in One SEO for WordPress (AIOSEO)</a></li><li><a href=\"#SEMrush\">SEMrush</a></li><li><a href=\"#Google-Search-Console\">Google Search Console</a></li><li><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-admin/post.php?post=45634&amp;action=edit#MonsterInsights\">MonsterInsights</a></li><li><a href=\"#Google-Keyword-Planner\">Google Keyword Planner</a></li><li><a href=\"#RankMath\">RankMath</a></li><li><a href=\"#Ahrefs\">Ahrefs</a></li></ol>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"All-in-One-SEO-for-WordPress\">1. <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">All in One SEO for WordPress (AIOSEO)</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"339\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AIOSEO.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO - Best WooCommerce SEO Plugins\" class=\"wp-image-45636\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AIOSEO.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AIOSEO-300x145.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AIOSEO-600x291.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AIOSEO-124x60.png 124w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AIOSEO-186x90.png 186w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\"></a><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">AIOSEO</a> is the best SEO plugin for WooCommerce store. With this plugin, you can easily optimize your WooCommerce store pages, products, categories, and more.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The plugin has over <strong>2 million</strong> active installations and the best part &#8211; you can set up this plugin on your website in less than <strong>10 minutes</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s see some of the best features of this plugin that give it a clear edge over the competition.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features</strong><strong>:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Generate SEO-Friendly Titles:</strong> Generate the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/using-the-smart-tags-in-titles-and-descriptions/\">titles and descriptions</a> for all product and category pages of the store.</li><li><strong>Optimize Individual Products:</strong> Helps you optimize each product, category, and tag archive page to maximize the chances of being featured high in Google search results.</li><li><strong>Image Optimization:</strong> Get full control over the optimization of the images that you upload to your store.</li><li><strong>Advanced Sitemaps:</strong> It offers different sitemap options, including Google News sitemap, smart sitemap, and video SEO sitemap.</li><li><strong>WooCommerce Support:</strong> The plugin offers several unique features that ensure that the WooCommerce store is fully optimized to capture the top search engine results positions.</li><li><strong>Seamless Integration: </strong>AIOSEO seamlessly integrates with popular social platforms such as Facebook, Twitter, Pinterest, YouTube, LinkedIn, Instagram, and more.</li><li><strong>TruSEO Score:</strong> Displays a score out of 100 which gives you a gauge of how well each page or post is optimized</li><li><strong>Webmaster Tools: </strong>You can easily connect your WooCommerce store with Google Analytics, Google search console, Bing, Yandex, and other webmaster tools.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong><strong>:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The basic plan starts at $39.60 per year and comes with a lot of features. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"SEMrush\">2. <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/semrush/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Semrush</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/semrush/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"282\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/SEMRUSH.png\" alt=\"SEMRUSH\" class=\"wp-image-45637\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/SEMRUSH.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/SEMRUSH-300x121.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/SEMRUSH-600x242.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/SEMRUSH-149x60.png 149w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/SEMRUSH-223x90.png 223w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.semrush.com/prices/\"></a></p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/semrush/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Semrush</a> is a popular SEO tool that is used by almost every serious blogger, service provider, store owner, and business of all sizes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This tool helps you find organic keywords and come up with strategies to rank higher for these keywords. You can carry out in-depth keyword research so that you can identify the gaps in your optimization plan.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Moreover, you have full control over competitor research and can easily analyze what your competitors are doing so that you can fine-tune your store&#8217;s marketing strategy.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Keywords Research:</strong> Easily find the right business keywords for your online store.</li><li><strong>Powerful Tracking:</strong> Easily track keywords ranking and related parameters to streamline your SEO processes.</li><li><strong>Link Building Opportunities:</strong> Discover the link profile of your competition to find out new opportunities for building links.</li><li><strong>Simplified Social Media Management:</strong> You can schedule posts on social platforms such as Facebook, LinkedIn, Twitter, and track the performance of individual posts.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>Pro</strong> plan starts at $119.95 per month.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"Google-Search-Console\">3. <a href=\"https://search.google.com/search-console/about\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Google Search Console</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://search.google.com/search-console/about\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"244\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Google-Search-Console.png\" alt=\"Google Search Console\" class=\"wp-image-45640\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Google-Search-Console.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Google-Search-Console-300x105.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Google-Search-Console-600x209.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Google-Search-Console-172x60.png 172w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Google-Search-Console-258x90.png 258w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://search.google.com/search-console/about\"></a></p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://search.google.com/search-console/about\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Google Search Console</a> is a free tool by Google that helps store owners keep a close eye on their presence in Google search results. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The best part is the alert that it generates when Google is unable to crawl the store pages, This alert is a simple way of tracking page indexing issues.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The tool is popularly used to discover the keywords that the store is ranking for, with detailed reports on the clicks, impressions, and related parameters.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This data is presented in easy-to-read reports that allow you to quickly find out the keywords that you need to focus on, in order to improve search engine results position of your store.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To learn more, check out <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-google-search-console-to-your-wordpress-website/\">how to add Google Search Console to your website</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Detailed Data:</strong> Google Search Console collects a lot of information about your store including the number and frequency of clicks, impressions, and errors.</li><li><strong>Track Store Pages:</strong> With this tool, you can easily track the performance of individual pages and see how they rank for your business keywords.</li><li><strong>Data in a Glance:</strong> The tool presents all data in easy-to-understand graphs that filter and present data collected for as long as <strong>60</strong> days.</li><li><strong>Pages Position:</strong> It allows you to check the web page ranking for specific keywords.</li><li><strong>Index URL:</strong> You can add specific URLs that haven’t been indexed by Google.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s a free service offered by Google.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"MonsterInsights\">4. <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">MonsterInsights</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"657\" height=\"271\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/MonsterInsights.png\" alt=\"MonsterInsights\" class=\"wp-image-45641\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/MonsterInsights.png 657w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/MonsterInsights-300x124.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/MonsterInsights-600x247.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/MonsterInsights-145x60.png 145w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/MonsterInsights-218x90.png 218w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 657px) 100vw, 657px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\"></a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>MonsterInsights is the best Google Analytics plugin on the planet that lets you track organic traffic reports and other user details that help you grow your business.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The plugin allows you to use all the advanced capabilities of Google Analytics without having to handle complicated setup. Once done, the plugin presents the data in reports that you can easily understand and use to <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/ultimate-woocommerce-seo-guide/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">optimize your WooCommerce store</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>WooCommerce Dashboard:</strong> Use the unique WooCommerce store dashboard to quickly see all essential store performance data including conversion rate, total transactions, total revenue, average order value, and more.</li><li><strong>Google Analytics Dashboard:</strong> This plugin lets you see the analytics dashboard in the WordPress admin area without switching to Google Analytics.</li><li><strong>Performance and Optimization:</strong> You can enable Google Optimize for A/B testing, and for adjusting the speed and sample rate.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>The <strong>Plus</strong> plan starts at $99.50 per year with a 100% money-back guarantee. </li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"Google-Keyword-Planner\">5. <a href=\"https://ads.google.com/home/tools/keyword-planner/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Google Keyword Planner</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://ads.google.com/home/tools/keyword-planner/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"271\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Google-Keywords-Planner.png\" alt=\"Google Keyword Planner\" class=\"wp-image-45642\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Google-Keywords-Planner.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Google-Keywords-Planner-300x116.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Google-Keywords-Planner-600x232.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Google-Keywords-Planner-155x60.png 155w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Google-Keywords-Planner-232x90.png 232w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://ads.google.com/home/tools/keyword-planner/\"></a></p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://ads.google.com/home/tools/keyword-planner/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Google Keyword Planner</a> is a powerful tool that you can use to discover the keywords that might be missing from your current SEO lineup.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>While the tool is mainly targeted toward advertisers who wish to take advantage of the massive audience that Google has, it’s also a great tool for WooCommerce store owners who are looking for gaps in their keyword discovery.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It shows detailed information about keywords including estimated search volume, and the difficulty level.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Estimate Search Volume:</strong> You can easily find out the average monthly search volume of the keywords to gauge their potential to bring traffic to the store.</li><li><strong>Simple Reports:</strong> The tool offers simple reports that present only the basic information about keywords.</li><li><strong>Plan Ad Campaigns:</strong> See the cost-per-click (CPC) to find the right keywords for executing high-performing ad campaigns for your store.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>This tool is free to use. However, you need to have a Google Ads account in order to use Google Keyword Planner.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"RankMath\">6. <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/rank-math/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">RankMath</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/rank-math/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"277\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Rankmath.png\" alt=\"RankMath\" class=\"wp-image-45643\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Rankmath.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Rankmath-300x119.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Rankmath-600x237.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Rankmath-152x60.png 152w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Rankmath-227x90.png 227w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/seo-by-rank-math/\"></a></p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/rank-math/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">RankMath</a> is another WordPress SEO plugin that helps you optimize your WordPress store.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>RankMath offers a lot of advanced features in the premium version, which also has a free version with a limited set of features.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can set up the RankMath plugin more quickly in 6 steps as compared to the 12 steps required to set up the Yoast plugin. Compare that to just 4 steps when you opt for the AIOSEO plugin.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For more details, see our guide <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/yoast-vs-rank-math-vs-all-in-one-seo/\">Yoast vs Rank Math vs All in One SEO</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>User Friendly:</strong> This plugin is user-friendly and offers powerful features for better store optimization.</li><li><strong>Content Analysis:</strong> This plugin analyzes posts and store pages content to identify improvement areas.</li><li><strong>Keyword Placement:</strong> you can see immediate indications for the keyword placement opportunities.</li><li><strong>Complete Score:</strong> You get a score that signifies the status optimization of the pages and posts of the store.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The pro plan starts at <strong>$59 </strong>per year, and also offers a <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/seo-by-rank-math/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">free lite version</a> for those who are not ready to invest in the plugin.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"Ahrefs\">7. <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/ahrefs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Ahrefs</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/ahrefs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"259\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Ahrefs.png\" alt=\"Ahrefs\" class=\"wp-image-45644\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Ahrefs.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Ahrefs-300x111.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Ahrefs-600x222.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Ahrefs-162x60.png 162w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Ahrefs-243x90.png 243w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://ahrefs.com/\"></a></p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/ahrefs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Ahrefs</a> is a great SEO tool that is considered a great alternative to <strong>SEMRush</strong>. This tool is best suited for analyzing website keywords and carrying out effective competitor analysis.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Using this tool, you can check out where your target audience is coming from, and how you can improve the store’s SEO to get more sales.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In addition, Ahrefs lets you take advantage of the opportunities of finding the right keywords that could potentially increase the volume of the store traffic and sales.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Ahrefs and SEMRush both are the best SEO tools that you can use and identify your target audience.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Traffic Estimation:</strong> This plugin gives you a pretty accurate estimation of the competitor traffic that helps you choose the topics focusing on the right keywords</li><li><strong>Site Explorer:</strong> This feature allows you to check competitors&#8217; content and understand the structure that is driving the volume of the traffic on their website.</li><li><strong>Relevant Link Building Opportunities:</strong> Use Ahrefs to discover thousands of relevant opportunities for link exchange.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>Lite</strong> plan starts at <strong>$99</strong> per month.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Which SEO Plugin Is Best for WooCommerce?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>We have shown you some of the best WooCommerce SEO plugins and tools that you can use to make your store more SEO-friendly and get more traffic and sales.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, if you’re still unable to choose the right plugin for your store, we highly recommend opting for the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\">AIOSEO</a> plugin. It offers great features and advanced tools that you can use to make your WooCommerce store a serious edge.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this article helps you to find out the best plugin for your store. Meanwhile, you can also check out our guide on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-find-long-tail-keywords-and-increase-organic-traffic/\">how to find long-tail keywords</a> and increase organic traffic.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Not <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">using AlOSEO</a> yet? Get started today!</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/best-woocommerce-seo-plugins/\">7 Best WooCommerce SEO Plugins And Tools to Get More Traffic</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:53:\"https://aioseo.com/best-woocommerce-seo-plugins/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:82:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:49:\"How to Name Your Image Files for SEO in WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:152:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-name-image-files-for-seo-in-wordpress/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=how-to-name-image-files-for-seo-in-wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:72:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-name-image-files-for-seo-in-wordpress/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 01 Jul 2021 15:43:36 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"SEO Tips\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"image file naming\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Image SEO\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:23:\"optimize images for web\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=44883\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:440:\"<p>Do you want to know how to name image files for SEO? Properly naming your image file helps Google better understand your website and, as a result, your website could get better rankings in search results. In this article, we’ll&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-name-image-files-for-seo-in-wordpress/\">How to Name Your Image Files for SEO in WordPress</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Saud Razzak\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7665:\"<p>Do you want to know how to name image files for SEO?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Properly naming your image file helps Google better understand your website and, as a result, your website could get better rankings in search results.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this article, we’ll show you how to name your image files for SEO in WordPress.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>So let&#8217;s dig in.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Before going further, let&#8217;s see why the title of your image is important for SEO.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"Is-Image-Title-Important-for-SEO\">Is Image Title Important for SEO?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Yes, the image title is important because it helps your readers and Google understand what the image is about.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here’s what Google has to say about it.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><em>&#8220;Like many of the other parts of the page targeted for optimization, filenames are best when they&#8217;re short, but descriptive.&#8221;</em></strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>This means you need to make sure your image title should be descriptive and easy to understand so that readers and Google have a clear idea of the image’s content.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"How-to-Name-Image-Files-for-Improved-SEO\">How to Name Image Files for SEO</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are a few things that you need to keep an eye on when choosing an image file name and make your website more SEO-friendly.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>1. Find a Relevant Image</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Before giving a name to any image, you need to make sure the image you have chosen is the right fit for the section where you want to add it. Even if you have a good name for an image that is not relevant, your readers will find it difficult to make sense of your choice.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>While it is always great to have a customized image, chances are you do not always have the time to come up with a great-looking graphic. In such cases, you can opt for:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Images released under <strong>Creative Commons (CC)</strong> license.</li><li>Search <strong>Flickr </strong>(but remember to ask permission before using an image)</li><li>Use websites like <strong>Unsplash </strong>that offer free images.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>When using any image, make sure you have permission to use it. It is always a good practice to check the license to see if you can use the image or modify it.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s assume the article you have written is about <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ultimate-wordpress-seo-guide/\">WordPress SEO</a>, and you selected the correct image name, but the image you chose is more relevant to accounting than WordPress.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/f3ccbpb-XKHKO9DG2Myaifjs94QbXY6fj2iLAMFS0Xehusaq2oUwZZiApzPSxqWofzDsVhRbu6z_n2-4QjIgMxuAYzOvgAHSQ_DxLQABNJCNbbRED99Ea5fP6GGbhofjLNLLlvHy\" alt=\"WordPress SEO wrong image\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Now consider the following image:&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/1GdHANmyz5m0Ojzzsv1jOALfqaxWBRxQ4RSC2brX3rWq5cixRVgPua-n4gXAJ2zN-z6OxjoU0eyzlCHcIu1i1jLnG9LYjbCR2A64BpFa5OHrI5iL8uiXK-qn41VbXYnP_kG83wYm\" alt=\"WordPress SEO correct image\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The name of both the images is WordPress SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can see even with the correct image name, the first image does not go well with the idea of WordPress SEO. In contrast, the second image is perfectly understandable by the readers and search engines.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>2. Set SEO Friendly Image File Name</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Choosing the right image file is only half the battle, naming it is another equally important part of image SEO optimization.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, let&#8217;s take a look at the below image. What would be the best file name for it?</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/T-ZP7x-ovmCUC2qVNL8JOOoWRpz87BE2uTYo6Po9UsAGuks0IFhHyg9W0Wx3dat0Tt2wbH72vbtfW77E7ch_zwV6ZFLhpp52bBcncZVlpFRhowrFt_f_m2WC0rGJyUiJFWEIuBWJ\" alt=\"how to name image files for SEO\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Bad Image Name Example:&nbsp;</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>324oiu98.jpg</li><li>Dslkjdklfj.jpg</li><li>AIOSEO-dashboard-image-is-here-download-it-now.jpg</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Good Image Name Example:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>AIOSEO-Dashboard.jpg</li><li>Dashboard-AIOSEO.jpg</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"SEO-Image-Names-Dashes-or-Underscores\">3. Avoid Underscores and Use Dashes Instead</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Did you know Google doesn&#8217;t recommend using underscores? </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"240\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/naming-image-files.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-45107\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/naming-image-files.jpg 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/naming-image-files-300x103.jpg 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/naming-image-files-600x206.jpg 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/naming-image-files-175x60.jpg 175w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/naming-image-files-263x90.jpg 263w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You&#8217;ve read it right&#8230; when you name your image files, it&#8217;s always recommended to choose dashes or hyphens instead of underscores?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>See the example below:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Good Practice:</strong> Google-Image-SEO</li><li><strong>Bad Practice:</strong> Google_Image_SEO</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Similarly, it&#8217;s also recommended to use all lower cases for your image files. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"Remember-the-Alt-Text\">Bonus Tip: Don&#8217;t Forget the Alt Text</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Adding Alt text to your images is the best way to convey your message to search engine spiders. Google recommends that the Alt text should be present for each image, and it should describe the image.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Most importantly, Alt text offers another opportunity to target the keywords phrases and thus help improve image optimization. For more details, please visit <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-write-alt-text-for-images-for-seo-3-easy-tips/\">how to write Alt text for images for SEO</a>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here’s a screenshot on how to add Alt text to your WordPress images. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/y7WZrcobHfvABCcwqUJslhYTfg82TUGMz9o3rE-_t16nRZ-aheamP47V6R590covh84sAXhLhCO5Gs0upISCVfHBGfnm3vqQgQcMSwdYe_ENUvbpbPwQrdGiykaGPucJqFg9WSTS\" alt=\"\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>In the above image, you can see the <strong>Alt Text</strong> option that appears for every image. Here you can add your <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/how-to-add-keywords-and-meta-descriptions-in-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">focus keyphrase</a> with the description of the image.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>SEO is a serious game, and image optimization is an important aspect of making your website SEO friendly and <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/seo-hacks-to-grow-your-traffic/\">getting more targeted traffic</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>For easy WordPress SEO optimization, you can try <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">AIOSEO</a>, the best WordPress SEO plugin on the planet. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope you learned how to name image files for SEO, optimize them for your websites.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You may also want to check out our <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/wordpress-seo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">ultimate WordPress SEO guide</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>What are you waiting for? Get started with the most powerful <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\">WordPress AIOSEO plugin</a> today.&nbsp;</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-name-image-files-for-seo-in-wordpress/\">How to Name Your Image Files for SEO in WordPress</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:69:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-name-image-files-for-seo-in-wordpress/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:79:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:46:\"How to Add 307 Temporary Redirect in WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:156:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-307-temporary-redirect-in-wordpress/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=how-to-add-307-temporary-redirect-in-wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:74:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-307-temporary-redirect-in-wordpress/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 29 Jun 2021 18:55:28 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"All in One SEO Pack\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:22:\"307 temporary redirect\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:21:\"wordpress redirection\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=44656\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:433:\"<p>Do you want to know how and when to add 307 temporary redirect in WordPress? When you delete a page, it&#8217;s important that you set up a proper redirection method. Otherwise, people will still be able to find the deleted&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-307-temporary-redirect-in-wordpress/\">How to Add 307 Temporary Redirect in WordPress</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Saud Razzak\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14798:\"<p>Do you want to know how and when to add 307 temporary redirect in WordPress?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>When you delete a page, it&#8217;s important that you set up a proper redirection method. Otherwise, people will still be able to find the deleted page and land on it, which hurts user experience and SEO.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this post, we&#8217;ll show you how to set up 307 temporary redirect on your WordPress website without any fuss.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>So let&#8217;s dig in.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are some quick links to what we&#8217;ll cover in this article. If you’re in a hurry, you can jump directly to the section you want to read.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"#What-is-an-HTTP-307-Temporary-Redirect\">What is an HTTP 307 Temporary Redirect?</a></li><li><a href=\"#When-to-Use-307-Temporary-Redirect\">When to Use 307 Temporary Redirect?</a></li><li><a href=\"#Easily-Add-307-Redirects-in-WordPress\">Easily Add 307 Redirects in WordPress</a></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"What-is-an-HTTP-307-Temporary-Redirect\">What Is an HTTP 307 Temporary Redirect?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>307 Temporary Redirect indicates that the requested page is temporarily available on another location When this status is generated, the requested content is served from the new temporary location.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>When 307 redirection is enabled, search engines get to know that the redirection is temporary which helps you keep the ranking intact.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"When-to-Use-307-Temporary-Redirect\">When to Use 307 Temporary Redirect</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A common way of using 307 temporary redirect is when your site is undergoing maintenance. By setting up 307 redirect, you can temporarily redirect users to another resource on your website.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Another great way of using the redirect is when you are updating seasonal campaign pages. While you’re updating those pages, you can set up a 307 temporary redirect to send the visitors coming from the search engine to a related page.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"Easily-Add-307-Redirects-in-WordPress\">Easily Set Up 307 Redirects in WordPress</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>You can easily configure 307 redirect to your WordPress websites with the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\">AIOSEO</a> plugin.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With the plugin, you can set up several types of redirects, including:&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>301 Moved Permanently&nbsp;</li><li>302 Found</li><li>303 See Other</li><li>304 Not Modified&nbsp;</li><li>307 Temporary Redirect</li><li>308 Permanent Redirect</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>The redirect setup is pretty simple&#8230; You just need to carry out a few steps, and you’re done.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now let’s see how to add 307 temporary redirect to your WordPress website with the AIOSEO plugin.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>1. Install AIOSEO Plugin</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>First things first, install and activate the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">AIOSEO plugin</a> on your WordPress website. For more details, see the WPBeginner <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/step-by-step-guide-to-install-a-wordpress-plugin-for-beginners/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">guide on properly installing and setting up a WordPress plugin</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>2. Enable Redirect on Your Website</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Once installed and activated the plugin, navigate to <strong>All in One SEO » Redirects</strong>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> You need to use at least the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/#pricing-table\">PRO version</a> to enable the <strong>Redirection Manager</strong>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, enable redirection by clicking <strong>Activate Redirects</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"400\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/enable-redirect-on-your-site.jpg\" alt=\"Enable Redirects on Your Site\" class=\"wp-image-44671\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/enable-redirect-on-your-site.jpg 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/enable-redirect-on-your-site-300x164.jpg 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/enable-redirect-on-your-site-600x329.jpg 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/enable-redirect-on-your-site-110x60.jpg 110w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/enable-redirect-on-your-site-164x90.jpg 164w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can now go to the <strong>Redirect</strong> screen. Here you need to <strong>Add a New Redirection</strong> by filling out the three main components:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Source URL</li><li>Target URL</li><li>Redirect Type</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"345\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Add-a-New-Redirection.png\" alt=\"Add New Redirection\" class=\"wp-image-44674\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Add-a-New-Redirection.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Add-a-New-Redirection-300x148.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Add-a-New-Redirection-600x296.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Add-a-New-Redirection-122x60.png 122w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Add-a-New-Redirection-183x90.png 183w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Source URL</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>You need to add the <strong>URL </strong>you want to redirect from. Note that the <strong>URL </strong>you’re adding should not include the domain name.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, if the <strong>URL </strong>is https://example.com/my-source-page, you only need to add /my-source-page/</p>\n\n\n\n<p>See this example:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"511\" height=\"180\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Source-URL.png\" alt=\"Source URL\" class=\"wp-image-44677\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Source-URL.png 511w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Source-URL-300x106.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Source-URL-170x60.png 170w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Source-URL-256x90.png 256w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 511px) 100vw, 511px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Target URL</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the Target URL field, enter the <strong>URL </strong>you want the visitors to visit instead of the <strong>Source URL</strong>.&nbsp; This requires the same input without the domain (see above for the example).</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"498\" height=\"114\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Target-URL.png\" alt=\"Target URL\" class=\"wp-image-44678\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Target-URL.png 498w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Target-URL-300x69.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Target-URL-190x43.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Target-URL-393x90.png 393w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 498px) 100vw, 498px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Redirect Type</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>AlOSEO comes with multiple redirection options, including the 307 Temporary Redirect.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Select <strong>307 Temporary Redirect </strong>from the dropdown menu.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"356\" height=\"352\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Select-307-Temporary-Redirect-.png\" alt=\"307 Temporary Redirect\" class=\"wp-image-44679\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Select-307-Temporary-Redirect-.png 356w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Select-307-Temporary-Redirect--300x297.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Select-307-Temporary-Redirect--100x100.png 100w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Select-307-Temporary-Redirect--61x60.png 61w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Select-307-Temporary-Redirect--91x90.png 91w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 356px) 100vw, 356px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Add Redirect</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once done with your selection, simply click <strong>Add Redirect</strong>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"224\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Add-Redirect-Button.png\" alt=\"Add Redirect Button\" class=\"wp-image-44680\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Add-Redirect-Button.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Add-Redirect-Button-300x96.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Add-Redirect-Button-600x192.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Add-Redirect-Button-188x60.png 188w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Add-Redirect-Button-281x90.png 281w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Once added, the redirection will be visible in the table on the same screen, where you can easily manage all your redirects.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"160\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Redirect-Table.png\" alt=\"Visitors Table\" class=\"wp-image-44681\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Redirect-Table.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Redirect-Table-300x69.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Redirect-Table-600x137.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Redirect-Table-190x43.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Redirect-Table-394x90.png 394w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This is an excellent way of checking out how many visitors <strong>Hits</strong> the <strong>Source URL</strong> and navigated to the<strong> Target URL</strong>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"620\" height=\"144\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Visitors-Hits.png\" alt=\"Redirect Hits \" class=\"wp-image-44682\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Visitors-Hits.png 620w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Visitors-Hits-300x70.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Visitors-Hits-600x139.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Visitors-Hits-190x44.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Visitors-Hits-388x90.png 388w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Checking The Redirects</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO lets you easily check whether the redirect(s) you have set up is working.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For this check, all you need to do is to hover the mouse pointer over the <strong>Source URL</strong> and click <strong>Check Redirect</strong>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"160\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Check-Redirect.png\" alt=\"Check Redirect\" class=\"wp-image-44683\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Check-Redirect.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Check-Redirect-300x69.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Check-Redirect-600x137.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Check-Redirect-190x43.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Check-Redirect-394x90.png 394w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Importing and Exporting Redirects</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO is the best SEO plugin for a reason; it offers exciting features that add significant value to your SEO initiatives.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>A popular option of the plugin is importing and exporting redirects from AIOSEO to other <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/best-seo-plugins-for-wordpress/\">SEO plugins</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For more details, see our guide on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/import-and-export-redirects-in-wordpress/\">how to easily import and export redirects in WordPress</a>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"620\" height=\"275\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/import-export.png\" alt=\"Import Export Redirect\" class=\"wp-image-44684\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/import-export.png 620w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/import-export-300x133.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/import-export-600x266.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/import-export-135x60.png 135w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/import-export-203x90.png 203w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that you know how to set up a redirect, it’s time to go into the details of some advanced settings::</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Redirect Methods — </strong>whether to set up the redirect at the code level or server level.</li><li><strong>Logs — </strong>to keep a record of the redirect requests.</li><li><strong>IP Logging — </strong>whether full or partial logging of IP addresses is needed that access your website.</li><li><strong>Automatic Redirects —</strong> to set up automatic redirects for posts and pages.</li><li><strong>HTTP Cache Header — </strong>to enable HTTP cache header.</li><li><strong>Redirect Defaults — </strong>set up default option for redirect requests.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"620\" height=\"275\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Redirect-Settings.png\" alt=\"Redirect Settings\" class=\"wp-image-44685\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Redirect-Settings.png 620w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Redirect-Settings-300x133.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Redirect-Settings-600x266.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Redirect-Settings-135x60.png 135w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Redirect-Settings-203x90.png 203w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>That’s all!&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope with the help of the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">AIOSEO plugin</a>, you can easily set up 307 Temporary Redirect. You can go ahead and check out the AIOSEO redirects feature and share your experience with us.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You may also want to check out our post on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-setup-bulk-301-redirects-in-wordpress/\">how to set up bulk 301 redirects in WordPress</a> and <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-easily-find-and-fix-404-errors-in-wordpress/\">how to easily find and fix 404 errors</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>What’re you waiting for? Get started with the most powerful <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\">WordPress AIOSEO plugin</a> today.&nbsp;</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-307-temporary-redirect-in-wordpress/\">How to Add 307 Temporary Redirect in WordPress</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:71:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-307-temporary-redirect-in-wordpress/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:79:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";